<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="1382" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="43.[178,1085,517,598]" pageId="43" pageNumber="1382">
Two new species are placed here, 
<emphasis box="[546,678,517,539]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="1382">S. breviatum</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[734,843,518,539]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="1382">S. opacum</emphasis>
. They possess aedeagi similar to those in members of the 
<emphasis box="[557,707,547,568]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="1382">S. binaluanum</emphasis>
group, differ however by a tubular sclerotized structure in the proximal part of the internal sac.
</paragraph>
